09/03/2010
HAKKARI, Turkey -- One soldier was killed and three were injured in a bomb blast in the southeast province of Hakkari on Tuesday (March 9th). 
The toll was the same Monday, when a bomb exploded in the same region as a convoy passed. 
Local security forces blame the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party. 
(DHA, Hurriyet - 09/03/10; TRT, Xinhua, Hurriyet, CNN Turk - 08/03/10)
